com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage

Class AdobePhotoAsset

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePhoto
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePhotoAsset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class AdobePhotoAsset
extends AdobePhoto
implements java.io.Externalizable
    An asset is a single photo or video (when supported). Each asset has one or more revisions. A revision can contain multiple files or renditions of the asset. The user who creates the first revision of an asset is the owner of that asset. Users can query, revise, and set favorite status for any assets that belong to a catalog that the caller shares. Users can also delete assets in a catalog they share.

      • create

        public static AdobePhotoAsset create(java.lang.String name,
                                     AdobePhotoCollection collection,
                                     java.net.URI path,
                                     java.lang.String type,
                                     IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobePhotoAsset,com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> photoCreationCallback)
        Creates (uploads) a new asset and adds it to a collection on the Adobe Photo service asynchronously. For an image file: preview, standard, and 2x thumbnail renditions are generated automatically.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the asset.
        collection - the collection to add the asset into.
        path - the local path to the data. The path must be locally valid and cannot be null.
        type - the content-type of the asset. The content-type is required and cannot be null.
        photoCreationCallback - informs the client of the create,error,progress and cancel events.
        Returns:
        the new asset created.

      • uploadMasterDataFromPath

        public void uploadMasterDataFromPath(java.net.URI path,
                                     boolean autoGenerateRenditions,
                                     IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobePhotoAsset,com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> uploadDataCallback)
        Uploads the master data (limited to 200MB) of this asset on the Adobe Photo Service asynchronously. Since the connection may be unstable, we recommend that the data be no more than 20MB.
        Parameters:
        path - the path to the master data. The path must be locally valid and cannot be null.
        autoGenerateRenditions - if renditions should be automatically generated.
        uploadDataCallback - informs client of upload related events.
